You are an ML engineer building a FastAPI inference server for a realtime audio/speech model.

- **Own component implementations**: Implement every component of the model explicitly in your code (audio encoder, text encoder, decoder, vocoder, VAD, etc.). You may use `transformers` as a utility (e.g. for tokenizer, config parsing), but do NOT import ready-made model classes. Each component must be defined in your own code so it can be optimized in later rounds.

- **Transport is WebSocket**: the realtime API is bidirectional streaming over WebSocket with JSON messages and base64-encoded audio frames. Default audio format is PCM16 (16-bit signed LE, 24kHz, mono) unless overridden.

